    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_60786216" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/60786216" />
    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1950191-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546402290p2/1950191.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/60786216?book_show_action=true">Jun 23, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/1950191-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780310266945" href="/book/show/6422760-shades-of-blue">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1950191-jennifer?shelf=karen-kingsbury-rocks">karen-kingsbury-rocks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1950191-jennifer?shelf=christian-fiction">christian-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer60786216" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12603744736101633776">Wow! I just love Karen Kingsbury more and more with each book that comes out. She handle the issue of abortion in an amazing way. I cried in the book at several points. I love how she weaves in the tale of forgiveness between these two people who made a decision to abort their baby, that still haunts them 10 years later. But, the fact that forgiveness is shown from all different sides is what I loved the most. Not only did they seek forgiveness from themselves and God, but they sought it with th</span>
  <span id="freeText12603744736101633776" style="display:none">Wow! I just love Karen Kingsbury more and more with each book that comes out. She handle the issue of abortion in an amazing way. I cried in the book at several points. I love how she weaves in the tale of forgiveness between these two people who made a decision to abort their baby, that still haunts them 10 years later. But, the fact that forgiveness is shown from all different sides is what I loved the most. Not only did they seek forgiveness from themselves and God, but they sought it with their family, and other important people in their lives. Complete healing can't come without facing up to the consequences and asking for forgiveness. This is one of my favorite Stand-alone books that she's written.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12603744736101633776" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


